Text.Value: Half-right, sharp-eyes - a Zhent is a normal trader. Just a matter of what's for sale.

EditorData.NodeContext: Impressed and appraising the player - but correcting your assumption. (Pronounced z-HENT)

Text.Value: No judgement, no right and wrong - just good deals and bad. That a problem for you?

EditorData.NodeContext: Affable, reasonable - laying out the situation for you and inviting you to take it or leave it.

Text.Value: Leave.
Let me see your wares.
Let me see your wares.
No problem at all. Let me see your wares.
I have no interest in trading with a Zhent.
See? Just business.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tone is 'that wasn't so hard, was it?'

Text.Value: Let me see your wares.
Let me see your wares.
What business do you have in a goblin camp?
Pleasure.

EditorData.NodeContext: Affable.

Text.Value: Now - much obliged for the chat, but I'm here to trade.

EditorData.NodeContext: Insincere about the chat - she's just Impatient to get back to the matter at hand.

Text.Value: It's slaves you're buying - not prisoners.
*You recognise the crest she bears - the winged serpent of the Zhentarim.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Camera should show Crest of Zhentarim she is wearing
EditorData.CinematicObjects: Crest of Zhentarim (worn by Roah Moonglow)

Text.Value: You joking? Goblins sell the best prisoners - cheap, quiet, and eager to be elsewhere.

EditorData.NodeContext: You've made the assumption that there's nothing worth trading with goblins - she's the expert correcting you. As if giving tips to a novice

Text.Value: You're no normal trader, are you? You're part of the Black Network.
Oh dry your eyes, Ilmater. It's me or a goblin cookpot - I know which I'd choose.

EditorData.NodeContext: Scornful but not overly so - she's more bored of your moralising than anything. Ilmater (ihl-MAY-ter) is a god of compassion and martyrdom. She has no time for your bleeding heart - she's all pragmatism.

Text.Value: Let me see your wares.
You Zhentarim tend to trade in misery - that why you're at a goblin camp?
Let me see your wares.
Bit quieter, if you please. This crowd just burned that inn to the ground, you might recall.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hushing you, looking around - you've said that others from her organisaton have run afoul of the very goblins all around you.

Text.Value: I killed your friends at Waukeen's Rest - is that a problem?
All I need to - there's an awful lot of folk flowing that way, and coin is sure to follow.

EditorData.NodeContext: She doesn't share your curiosity - but she sees the opportunity for business in Moonrise.

Text.Value: Folk up here like to quiver over right and wrong - until the coin starts clinking, anyway.

EditorData.NodeContext: A hint of contempt - her organisation is reviled for dealing in drugs, weapons etc, but it's often the same people who are buying from them.

Text.Value: I knew the Zhent were heartless, but the goblin slave trade? Really?
Leave.
Need something?

EditorData.NodeContext: Friendly, casual.

Text.Value: But the Black Network pays like for like. They - we - will be after you now.

EditorData.NodeContext: Warning you, stating a fact but almost pitying you.

Text.Value: ... assuming I believe you - not really, no. Never much liked Zarys, truth be told.

EditorData.NodeContext: Smiling, dangerous. You've just goaded her with the fact that you killed members of her organisation. She's passionless when it comes to business, but even so her organisation is known for exacting vengeance on anyone who harms a member.

Text.Value: Your insignia; I've seen it before - in the Underdark.
Might have to find my faith and see this Absolute for myself, eh?

EditorData.NodeContext: Speculative, joking - she'll happily pretend to be relgious if it means making a deal

Text.Value: Already turned quite the profit today, so I'm feeling generous.

EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to coax you into a deal

Text.Value: Still some deals to be done here, though - you want to trade, or what?

EditorData.NodeContext: Eyeing you up, bringing you back to the topic at hand

Text.Value: But for now, I see no reason we can't make a civilised trade. I reckon you'll be wanting some steel.

EditorData.NodeContext: A cold threat behind her words. You've made a huge mistake and you're too stupid to even realize, but you're so little of a threat to her that she may as well trade with you one last time.

Text.Value: Reckon we've said all there is to say, eh? But don't worry - the Network'll be in touch soon.

EditorData.NodeContext: Icy, faux-friendly - she and her organisation are sworn, if polite, enemies of yours now

Text.Value: Your insignia; I've seen it before - in the Underdark.
Leave.
Aye, so you have. It's one place the Zhentarim can trade openly, thank the gods.

EditorData.NodeContext: Pleasantly surprised at your recognition of her. (Pronounced z-HENT-ah-rim)

Text.Value: Ah - need something then, do you?

EditorData.NodeContext: Tone is 'well look who we have here?' This response is if the player refused to trade with her previously out of principle.

Text.Value: Leave.
I'm not interested in trading with a Zhent.
Leave.
Not my concern, so long as I'm paid. Speaking of - something to trade, or what?

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrugging, getting back to the matter at hand. She's used to minding her own business - and everything is just business to her.

Text.Value: But good - that means Zarys and her little operation weren't found.

EditorData.NodeContext: ZAR-iss. Thoughtful, getting your measure again - you've proven more capable than she'd have assumed

Text.Value: Already turned quite the profit today, so I'm feeling generous.

EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to coax you into a deal

Text.Value: What business does a Zhent have with goblins?
Till next time.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tone is 'that wasn't so hard, was it?'

Text.Value: Suit yourself. You'll be back when you have need - just make sure you have coin, too.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not bothered one way or the other. She's bored of moral posturing about her trade, and she'll happily do a deal once you get over yourself

Text.Value: Ask that kin of yours they're all bowing to. The glint in her eye is bad news for someone.
Ask the drow they're all bowing to. That glint in her eye is bad news for someone.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrug - it's not her problem, but she pities whoever the drow is planning to deal with.

Text.Value: I've already done business with your kind - beneath Waukeen's Rest.
Already turned quite the profit today, so I'm feeling generous.
Let me see your wares.
Weapons and other... exotic goods, true enough. But most of all, we offer discretion.

EditorData.NodeContext: Explaining her trade, the benefits of dealing with her organisation. She sells illicit goods but she sees it as a trade just like any other, just a matter of perspective

Text.Value: What do the goblins want smokepowder for?
What business does someone like you have in a goblin camp?
Till this crowd converted and started sending their captives to Moonrise Towers, at least.

EditorData.NodeContext: Correcting herself. Tone is rueful - some of her best trading partners have fallen to organised religion.

Text.Value: No complaints, mind - I just sold enough smokepowder to cover the loss ten times over.

EditorData.NodeContext: Perking up - she still managed to make a profit. Always a bright side.

Text.Value: What do you know about Moonrise Towers?
Leave.
It's just business. If there was money in being good, the Zhentarim would be pure as paladins.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrugging, bemused at how infamous her organisation is for dealing in the black market. If people weren't buying, they wouldn't be selling./

Text.Value: That the jingle of coin I hear? You've timed it well, my friend.

EditorData.NodeContext: Warm and welcoming (a kind of mercantile 'Who do we have here?')

Text.Value: Let me see your wares.
Need something else?

EditorData.NodeContext: Friendly, casual.

Text.Value: Be seeing you. Sooner than you'd like, I expect.

EditorData.NodeContext: Smiling, threatening.

Text.Value: Leave.
Seems you're a friend of the family. That warrants a discount - a small one.

EditorData.NodeContext: Coming to a decision about you - she'll give you a discount seeing as you helped her friends out.

Text.Value: Leave.
Your insignia; I've seen it before - in the Underdark.
Ah, the family friend! Need something?

EditorData.NodeContext: Welcoming you back, you've done her a good turn.

Synopsis: A trader from the Zhentarim (z-HENT-ah-rim) , a shady organisation of spies, assassins and dealers in illicit goods. The player may or may not recognise her as such, but either way her attitude is blunt, breezy and unscrupulous. She's there to make money, and you're either there to make a deal or wasting her time - she has absolutely no interest in indecision or moralizing.
